  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Designer",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Job Description:</strong></h3><p>We are seeking a highly skilled and experienced Graphic Designer to lead our design efforts across various mediums. The ideal candidate will have a strong portfolio showcasing expertise in graphic design (both static and animated), event fabrication mock-ups, and web design. This role demands creativity, attention to detail, and the ability to manage multiple projects simultaneously.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Create visually compelling static and animated graphics for various platforms, including print, digital, and social media</li><li>Develop branding materials, including logos, brochures, posters, and other marketing collateral</li><li>Ensure all designs align with Skills Development Academy and our clients' branding and messaging guidelines</li><li>Design and create mock-ups for event setups, including stages, booths, and other event-related structures</li><li>Collaborate with the events team to understand requirements and deliver designs that enhance the overall event experience</li><li>Design and maintain Skills Development Academy and our clients' websites, ensuring user-friendly experiences and visually appealing layouts</li><li>Work closely with web developers to implement design changes and updates</li><li>Create wireframes, prototypes, and final designs for new web pages and features</li></ul><p><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum of 5 years of experience in graphic design, with a strong portfolio showcasing static and animated designs, event fabrication mock-ups, and web design projects</li><li>Proficiency in Adobe Creative Suite (Photoshop, Illustrator, After Effects, etc.), Sketch, Figma, or other relevant design tools</li><li>Experience with 3D modeling and rendering software (e.g., SketchUp, Blender) is a plus</li><li>Strong understanding of web design principles, including UX/UI</li><li>Good communication and collaboration skills</li><li>Detail-oriented with a passion for delivering high-quality work</li></ul><p><strong>Working Hours & Days: </strong></p><ul><li>Monday - Friday (9:00 am - 6:00 pm) </li></ul>",
